---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What drone cinematography services does SkyWyo offer?",
    a: "SkyWyo provides four core services: aerial cinematography up to 8K ProRes RAW on FAA Part 107 certified platforms; matched ground and gimbal photography on ARRI Alexa Mini LF; director-led editing with principal film, social cut, and showcase loop; and Dolby Vision color grading with print-grade stills included in every production."
  },
  {
    q: "What areas of Wyoming does SkyWyo serve?",
    a: "We operate statewide from hubs in Casper and Laramie. Regular production territories include Jackson Hole, Teton Village, Big Horn County, Sheridan, Cody, Pinedale, Lander, and Wind River Country. All FAA airspace authorizations are managed by our team."
  },
  {
    q: "Is SkyWyo FAA certified and insured?",
    a: "Yes. All SkyWyo pilots hold FAA Part 107 Remote Pilot Certificates required for commercial drone operations. The studio is fully insured and bonded for every production, including liability coverage for BLM, private ranch, and residential operations."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does a production cost?",
    a: "Each project is scoped individually. Ranch-scale multi-day productions differ significantly from focused residential commissions. We do not publish fixed pricing. All inquiries receive a response within 24 hours with a production outline and investment range."
  },
  {
    q: "How long does a production take from brief to delivery?",
    a: "The standard timeline is 17–30 days: a 7–14 day environmental study period to identify peak light conditions, a 3-day principal shoot window, and a 13–17 day edit and delivery phase. Rush delivery within 24–48 hours is available for qualifying projects."
  },
  {
    q: "What formats do you deliver?",
    a: "Standard delivery includes an H.265 master, a ProRes proxy, a social-format cut, a silent showcase loop suitable for property displays, print-grade stills, and Dolby Vision HDR and SDR versions. Two rounds of revision are included in every production."
  }
];
---

<section class="page-px py-30 md:py-[160px] border-t border-rule" id="faq">
  <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-20 md:gap-[80px]">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
        <span class="font-mono text-[var(--text-xs)] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-paper-dim">Questions</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="serif text-[clamp(32px,3.4vw,56px)] leading-[1.08] tracking-[-0.018em] max-w-[12ch]">
        What you need to <em class="italic text-[#d6c89f]">know.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-[var(--text-sm)] text-paper-dim leading-relaxed max-w-[30ch]">
        Common questions from ranch owners, real estate brokers, and architects considering a production.
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl class="flex flex-col divide-y divide-rule">
      {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
        <div class={`py-7 reveal delay-${Math.min(i, 3) * 75}`}>
          <dt class="text-[var(--text-base)] font-display font-medium text-paper leading-snug mb-3">{faq.q}</dt>
          <dd class="m-0 text-[var(--text-sm)] text-paper-dim leading-relaxed">{faq.a}</dd>
        </div>
      ))}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>
